article_text:
Hillary Clinton is having a bad week. Actually, we’ve discerned an emerging pattern: Every time a week has seven days, it turns out to be bad for Mrs. Clinton.

“Hillary Clinton is viewed more negatively now than at almost any time in her political career,” reports The Wall Street Journal. Jeb Bush is having trouble among Republicans too, but then he isn’t the inevitable nominee. More details from the WSJ/NBC News poll:
